Antique Moroccan Centre Table Hand Carved from Atlas Cedar

About the Item

Exceptional craftsmanship and uniquely beautiful wood, both of a bygone era. This 12-sided centre table or coffee table is constructed of Atlas Cedar. A wood unique to pockets of the Moroccan Atlas Mountains. An ornamental wood, highly prized for it''s honey amber colour, attractive fine and straight grain, as well as it''s workability. The 12-sided table top, the 12 side flanks and the 6 legs all feature ornate interconnected hand carvings in 3-dimensional organic and yet spectacularly symmetrical forms. Remarkable condition for the age. It has been painstakingly cleaned and restored without abrading any surfaces.

    By Hans J. Wegner, Arne Jacobsen, Eero Saarinen, Charles and Ray Eames
    Located in Grand Cayman, KY
    Very elegant 1960s round dining table Made in Denmark, unusually constructed from solid teak wood (not veneered). Quintessential Scandinavian Modern design: minimal, fine materials, highly practical, clean smooth lines, sturdy construction and timeless aesthetic. In round form, the table has a diameter of 48 in (122 cm) and a single leg, which achieves an uncluttered appearance under the table and buttressing into four feet that rise a low profile parallel to the floor. This leg form in teak bears a striking resemblance to the iconic La Fonda base by Charles Eames, cast in Aluminium. We have pictured them together. In extended dining form, the table has a length of either 87 in (220 cm) or 67 in (171 cm). The width remains at 48 in (122 cm). The wooden elements of the table (top, legs and feet) bisect into two equal parts, each of a semi-circular top, leg and two feet. The extension mechanism is achieved by sliding these two symmetrical halves away from each other on metal rails hidden underneath and then inserting either one or two leaves onto the metal rails. Table height is standard 28.5 in (72 cm) in both round and extended formats. The ballerina legs are carved from solid teak while the top is a veneer of exceptional quality straight grain teak. The table retains it''s original finish in remarkable vintage condition with only extremely minor signs of wear. This timeless table shows every promise of gracing a kitchen or dining room for another 60 years, and then some. Disassembles to pack flat for efficient shipping.
